# 🏠 House Price Prediction

A regression-based ML model trained on 10,000+ real estate records to 
predict house prices with high accuracy — covering the full data science 
pipeline from raw data to deployment-ready model.

## 🔍 Overview
This project tackles real-world real estate pricing using multiple regression 
models. Through rigorous data cleaning, EDA, and feature engineering, it 
achieves a 15–20% reduction in prediction error compared to baseline models.

## ✨ Features
- Comprehensive EDA with visualizations
- Data cleaning and outlier handling
- Feature engineering (location encoding, size normalization)
- Model comparison across three algorithms
- Evaluation using RMSE, MAE, and R² metrics

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
`Python` `Pandas` `NumPy` `Scikit-learn` `XGBoost` `Matplotlib` `Seaborn`

## 📊 Results
- **15–20% reduction** in prediction error vs baseline
- Best model: XGBoost Regressor
- Metrics: RMSE, MAE, R²

